flow.mentorSays:
Let's understand what this Drag and Drop List challenge asks for.

**Challenge Description:**
const tasks = [
  { id: 1, text: "Task 1" },
  { id: 2, text: "Task 2" },
  { id: 3, text: "Task 3" }
];

// Requirements:
// - Drag tasks to reorder
// - Visual feedback during drag (opacity, cursor)
// - Drop to new position
// - Update list order
// - Works on touch devices (bonus)

// Can use native HTML5 DnD or library (react-beautiful-dnd)

**What we need to build:**
This challenge tests your understanding of DnD API, state updates.

**Time estimate:** 30 minutes
**Difficulty level:** Senior

This is a practical interview question that tests your understanding of core Angular concepts and your ability to implement them correctly.

